Looking at this, I'll build a real, working study tracker: a typed              
in‑memory-backed API (with a clear Supabase swap‑in point, kept out of the      
static import graph so the build never breaks if the package isn't installed),  
scoped per-visitor via an httpOnly cookie so one browser's sessions can never   
leak into another's, strict input validation with 400s on bad input, and a calm,
content-first UI with real loading/empty/error states and a weekly dashboard    
computed only from what was actually persisted.                                 

