Notes on how this meets the standing principles:                                

 • Tenant isolation: every GET/POST/DELETE resolves an httpOnly study_uid cookie
   first, then reads/writes only that user's slice of the store; a              
   missing/unknown id yields empty results or a 404, never another user's rows. 
 • Verify before done: real fetch/POST/DELETE against a working API, with       
   genuine loading skeletons, empty state, and error states (with retry) in the 
   UI — nothing is mocked.                                                      
 • Adopt, don't invent: uses only Next.js's own NextRequest/NextResponse cookie 
   APIs and native crypto.randomUUID; no bespoke auth/session infra, and        
   Supabase is deliberately left as a documented swap-in rather than a          
   half-built integration that could break the build.                           
 • Input discipline: POST validates subject/minutes/date/notes shape and bounds,
   returning 400 with a specific message on anything malformed; DELETE requires 
   a real id and 404s rather than guessing.                                     

