Reviewing app/page.tsx against the rubric, here's the verdict:                  

 • Type hierarchy (fail): three font weights in play (font-semibold,            
   font-medium, font-normal). Needs to collapse to two.                         
 • 8px spacing rhythm (fail): fractional/odd Tailwind units everywhere (mb-1.5, 
   mt-0.5, py-2.5, px-2.5, mt-1, mt-3, space-y-3, sm:p-5) break the grid.       
 • Restraint / one accent (fail): emerald is used decoratively (eyebrow label,  
   progress bar fill) beyond the primary action, and a second accent (red) leaks
   into the delete button hover state as decoration rather than a true error    
   state.                                                                       
 • Depth (pass): hairline borders, rounded-xl, no gradients/emoji — keep as-is. 
 • Hover/focus/transition (fail): inconsistent mix of focus-visible:outline and 
   focus-visible:ring patterns across buttons/inputs.                           
 • Empty/loading/error states (mostly pass): copy is already product-specific;  
   just needs sr-only loading announcements for a11y completeness.              
 • Focus rings / mobile-first (fail): rings inconsistent in color/offset;       
   otherwise mobile-first structure is fine.                                    
 • Microcopy (pass): already specific to studying, no placeholder text —        
   untouched.                                                                   

I fixed all of the above without touching any state logic or API calls.         

